  "changelog": [
    {
      "version": "2.9.0",
      "date": "2026-07-10",
      "summary": "v2.9.0 — LayoutCanvas modularization: the 513KB LayoutCanvas.tsx monolith is split into 69 modules ≤15KB under layout-canvas/ (58 mechanical Phase-1 extractions + Phase-2 orchestrator decomposition into domain features, 3 views, canvas-io, and two coarse hooks per the architecture-critic-approved seam — see docs/architect-handoff-layoutcanvas-split.md). Behavior-preserving; verified by adversarial review (2 state-survival fixes applied), tsc gate held at the 10 pre-existing baseline errors throughout. 24KB of confirmed-dead components deleted (SettingsModal, FullModal, ThemesPanelContent, LayersPanelContent, OverridesPanelContent). Every pinned file now fits a single-call delivery; the multi-slice chunk grind is dead. Supersedes the v2.8.3 stamp plan (PR #47 closed unmerged; its recorded publish_hash 42901362 was already stale). publish_hash 017bf873 (prod deploy 2026-07-10, delivered via the v2.9.0 per-module update loop; pin 79d8995)."
    },
    {
      "version": "2.8.3",
      "date": "2026-07-09",
      "summary": "v2.8.3 — make honest sweeps possible on real installs. (1) preview/App.tsx and preview/pages/* removed from app_files: the install flow copies the TARGET app's pages into preview/pages/ and patches App.tsx per install (workbench-install.md §7c/7d), so these are per-install working state — pinning the CarboNet samples guaranteed a C2 mismatch on every used install (found live on ISO Tracker). proxy.ts/Nav.tsx/Toast.tsx stay pinned (canonical, never patched). (2) server.ts now imports the platform-provided ./ai module at the entry point — GlideOS supplies ai.ts in every workspace and the ISO Tracker build fails without the entry-file import; pinning it removes the third false-mismatch class. publish_hash is null pending the first prod deploy of this version (C3 fails closed until recorded — see ADR-006)."
    },
    {
      "version": "2.8.2",
      "date": "2026-07-08",
      "summary": "v2.8.2 — fix members.map crash on non-array /app-api/members responses. A 500 from /app-api/members (transient Neon pool exhaustion) resolves r.json() to an error object, which useQuery caches; members.map then crashes the SPA. Coerce non-array payloads to [] at both fetch sites (LayoutCanvas.tsx). Found live by the canary agent during the v2.8.1 /update. publish_hash 40377c21 (prod deploy of this fix); pin 6ec4fb6 (main merge of PR #34)."
    },
    {
      "version": "2.8.1",
      "date": "2026-07-08",
      "summary": "ADR-005 — seeding is agent-only; SPA auto-seed reversed. The browser cache-seed shipped in 2.8.0 (ADR-003/004) is removed: the installer scaffold proxy's license gate requires the real GlideOS identity, which only the in-editor agent has (the browser sends org_id='default' → 403; the worker is 522-blocked), so the SPA path could never seed. Removed the boot auto-seed, the force-push browser-relay panel, fetchSeedConfig/seedPathsFromPin, and the /admin/seed-config route (ADR-004 superseded). design_file_cache is seeded exclusively by the agent at install/update. Also records the first real publish_hash (0f98d591, prod deploy of this reversal) so the C3 deploy-fingerprint gate can run — closes the ADR-006 fail-closed 503 on c3/trigger. Live-DB fix (not code): UNIQUE(action_key) added to the installer's design_console_actions, fixing the 42P10 on /update/begin."
    },
    {
      "version": "2.8.0",
      "date": "2026-07-06",
      "summary": "ADR-003 — bundle-free delivery. Source is no longer baked into source-bundle*.ts; the four bundles are dropped from app_files (delivery) and git-removed. design_file_cache is filled from the pinned public manifest-hashes.json, relayed by the browser through the installer scaffold proxy (worker→worker HTTP is 522-blocked): the SPA auto-seeds any missing/stale pinned path on boot, verifying every file's sha256 against the pin server-side before write (idempotent upsert self-heals partial caches). force-push reworked to reseed-then-push-all (aborts if any file fails to relay). Unpinned docs (AGENTS.md/PROJECT_NOTES.md/PREFERENCES.md) keep flowing through the trusted agent /admin/file-cache channel only — the browser seed endpoint has no skip-list (every file pin-verified). Generator renamed generate-source-bundles.mjs → gen-manifest-hashes.mjs (bundle generation removed; --check adds a 15000-byte ratchet gate). LayoutCanvas.tsx NOT split this release — it ships as a multi-slice legacy file; split deferred to a canary-driven decision. NOTE: commit + manifest-hashes restamped by gen-manifest-hashes.mjs at release; publish_hash set after the prod deploy (C3)."
